Dio Modern. Mediterranian is a little stretch, but the idea is there and strong. The Souvlaki, while not reminding me of Greek food, was good. There was a weird oniony creamy spread type addition that tasted good, but I was not familiar with. It was not baba ghanoush or hummus, but may have been a greek spread I haven't met yet. Either way, I was not upset it graced my plate. This would have been a 3 star review if I hadn't tried a cocktail. The Dios Mojito. It was a nice fruity riff on the standard mojito, and because I am nothing if not thorough in my objective reviewing, I got a second to make sure the first was not a fluke. Neither were flukes. Or both were. Either way, they were delicious. 4 stars for my best food experience in Tampa so far.

The Dio Mediterranean restaurant is located in downtown Tampa on the corner of Franklin Street and Twiggs. It offers a wide variety of Mediterranean dishes. The menu includes many salads and appetizers to choose from. They also have entrees, wraps and bowls. I decided to try one of their bowls and ordered the Mediterranean bowl. It came with tabuli, babghaanoush, falafel, fresh greens and sliced beets. You can add a protein for an additional charge. I decided to add gyro meat. All the ingredients were fresh and it was a tasty meal. The Falafel stole the show. The pieces were huge, and more importantly tasted delicious. Served with tahini sauce of course. If the rest of the meal had been subpar, I still would have rated the meal three stars because of the awesome Falafel. They also have beer, wine, and evening entertainment. Very good experience and will definitely return.

Spanakopita is a phyllo dough (similar to puff pastry) filled with spinach and feta cheese with some great spices and served with a light yogurt dip. I added 2 Fallafes for protein. Then the same guy came back with a leaf blower and was blowing stuff out from under the tables, 3 feet away, while we’re ordering and drinking cocktails. I will NEVER return; I am floored the restaurant staff would be this uncaring. Last night may have been the single worst customer service experience I have ever had. It was a friend of mine's birthday a couple days ago and due to it being at the beginning of the week, we decided to celebrate last night. We made our first stop, had our fun, and once done we proceeded to Dio. Said friend made reservations earlier in the week, Tuesday I believe, for our group of ten. We arrived, were promptly seated, and everything was fine. Then somebody who worked there came up and told us we had to move outside because somebody else had reservations and they specifically asked to be seated inside versus outside. We were all pretty miffed at this point because we were seated, already ordered drinks, were preparing to order appetizers, etc. The other party of ten that asked to be seated inside, allegedly, was nowhere to be seen. So, all ten of us head outside and see them setting up our "table". I use the word table in quotations because I can't think of a better word. It was a row of two-person tables in the middle of the sidewalk, segregated from the rest of the customers, and blocking the walkway for pedestrians. I wish I had taken pictures. There was a car parked on the curb and if the owners had returned to the vehicle, two or three of us at that table would have had to get out of our seats and move to allow them in. We basically said, "Screw this. We're out." This seating arrangement was unacceptable and by the time we left, the other group that allegedly had reservations and allegedly asked to be seated inside whereas we didn't when we made our reservations, still hadn't shown up. Several of us asked to speak to the manager. The person we were speaking to refused. From what I gather, they knew that they were in the wrong or they would get fired for pulling that stunt. Why turn down a ten-top THAT HAS RESERVATIONS? Not that it matters, but I'll never return to Dio. I'd rather just walk a block and down and grab a couple slices from Eddie and Sam's, which is what we ended up doing anyway.

Like others have said, atrocious service. Literally maybe the worst I've ever had. My wife and I sat down, and from the time the server took our order it took 25 minutes to get our drinks. The server had offered to comp an app earlier, which we accepted, and when the bill came the item was still there. Meanwhile the owner is schmoozing with the regulars instead of trying to ensure his patrons arent miserable. Want to know a bad way to make regulars? Awful service, literally the worst. A shame. The food is decent, and we live 10 minutes walking distance away. Would have loved to find a new spot to frequent. But this is a hard pass.
